description: Andre Krayewski's debut comic series, detailing his experiences as a young artist in Stalinist Poland - dodging the draft, chasing beautiful women, and yearning for a better life in an America that only existed in films, jazz songs, and his dreams.

The Enemy of my Enemy is my Friend

The knockout dark historical fantasy series of the Irish War for Independence continues. In this all-important issue Michael Collins is saved, earns a friendship and reveals the reason for the War.
name: The Enemy of My Enemy Is My Friend

description:
A secret government agency is developing state-of-the-art weapons for use by a soon-to-be-created squad of fireman/policeman-hybrid officers - Tactical Rescue Evacuation Police - or TREP officers.

But things don't go as planned when one inventor snaps, robs the laboratory, and uses the TREP technologies to wreak havoc upon the city. The remaining members of Project TREP test their courage trying to save the city from their former colleague gone mad.

Being faced with a horrible blizzard during their journey, a beautiful widow named Joy and her party are forced to stay at Castle Campion for a while. Earl Campion seems rather pleased because he now has guests on the day before Christmas when he expected to spend it alone. Joy has spent her life not relying on men, but she can't help but admire how confident and sophisticated he is. Meanwhile the earl seems to have noticed her, as well...
name: Vol. 1

description:
What do we really know about those who are closest to us? What deep-rooted secrets do they conceal from us? And if we could discover the truth, would we even want to? Victims and Other Questions for an Empty Universe confronts these questions, and others, in 6 strange stories.

These stories will make want to leave the light on-so you can keep an eye on the person lying next to you.

Winner, Best Web Comic 2014

Horror Comics Awards

volume.name: Victims and Other Questions for an Empty Universe

description:
Mister Sinister was robbed of his prize — the Adamantium-covered body of Wolverine — when the X-Men stole it from his Finland fortress. But they left something behind — another piece of the puzzle, something else that was taken from our team. Now, Sinister has his revenge! And in the aftermath of his brutal attack, which heroes will remain standing — and who will not survive?! As the dust settles, the final pieces of the puzzle fall into place, and Mystique’s endgame stands fully revealed. But she’s not just trying to resurrect her long-lost love Destiny. Where does this leave the Wolverines? Find out how it all ends as everything comes crashing down!

Collects Wolverines #16-20.

description:
From the artist of Kimi ni Todoke comes another story of first love!

Seventeen year old Sachi Takamura has never had a boyfriend. When a sympathetic classmate arranges a group date, Sachi meets the charming and magnetic Yukihiro Miyamoto. It's instant attraction—until she hears that he's a sweet-talking playboy! Is he everything that the rumors promised, or is there more to him than meets the eye? Sachi sets out to win his heart and stumbles upon more than she bargained for...

description: Mountaineer Shiga made a promise to his best friend following his tragic death in the Himalayas. Twelve years later and he is called upon to honor that promise. But if the Mountains are unforgiving, then the City is treacherous! So, when Shiga comes down from his Mountain refuge to look for his friend's missing daughter Megumi, all he finds is trouble! Twice Eisner-nominated Taniguchi builds the tension to a massive climax in this exciting drama.
